{
  "text": "The Wilcoxon signed-rank test indicates that for a number of variables di\u00a4erent speci\u2026-cations of the regression model return diverse coe\u00a2 cient signs. Now, we are interested whether the sizes of the coe\u00a2 cients are statistically di\u00a4erent too. When estimating, for example, the impact of schools on house values such as in [CITATION_1] the sign of a variable is of interest but also its impact on house prices. Consequently, the question shall be answered if variable and model selection in \u2021uences the coe\u00a2 cients'sizes of the variables signi\u2026cantly.",
